org.microbean.jersey.netty

Class AbstractContainerRequestDecoder<T,H extends T,D extends T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.netty.channel.ChannelHandlerAdapter
      • io.netty.channel.ChannelInboundHandlerAdapter
        • io.netty.handler.codec.MessageToMessageDecoder<T>
          • org.microbean.jersey.netty.AbstractContainerRequestDecoder<T,H,D>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the common supertype of messages that can be decoded
    H - the type of "headers" messages
    D - the type of "data" messages
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ChannelHandler, ChannelInboundHandler
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Http2StreamFrameToContainerRequestDecoder, HttpObjectToContainerRequestDecoder

    public abstract class AbstractContainerRequestDecoder<T,H extends T,D extends T>
extends MessageToMessageDecoder<T>
    A MessageToMessageDecoder that decodes messages of a specific type into ContainerRequests.

    Instances of this class are normally followed in a ChannelPipeline by instances of the AbstractContainerRequestHandlingResponseWriter class.

    Author:
    Laird Nelson
    See Also:
    decode(ChannelHandlerContext, Object, List), MessageToMessageDecoder, ContainerRequest, AbstractContainerRequestHandlingResponseWriter

      • installMessage

        protected void installMessage(ChannelHandlerContext channelHandlerContext,
                              H message,
                              ContainerRequest containerRequest)
        Installs the supplied message into the supplied ContainerRequest in some way.

        This implementation calls ContainerRequest.setProperty(String, Object) with the fully-qualified class name of the headers class supplied at construction time as the key, and the supplied message as the value.

        Parameters:
        channelHandlerContext - the ChannelHandlerContext in effect; will not be null; supplied for convenience; overrides may (and often do) ignore this parameter
        message - the message to install; will not be null and is guaranteed to be a "headers" message
        containerRequest - the just-constructed ContainerRequest into which to install the supplied message; will not be null
